)F    FUNCTION - TO DO HEX AND DECIMAL INTEGER ARITHMETIC ON 3278/9
              CRT TERMINALS IN FULL-SCREEN MODE.

)X    SYNTAX - AR


   DESCRIPTION -

     THE PURPOSE OF THIS COMMAND IS TO DO HEX AND DECIMAL INTEGER
   ARITHMETIC IN FULL-SCREEN MODE ON 3278/9 CRT TERMINALS.  THE
   COMMAND IS MENU DRIVEN.

     IN ADDITION HEX AND DECIMAL ARITHMETIC, AN OPTION IS AVAILABLE
   TO DO HEX TO DECIMAL AND DECIMAL TO HEX CONVERSIONS.  ANOTHER
   OPTION GIVES THE USER THE ABILITY TO CONVERT 3270 SCREEN AND BUFFER
   ADDRESSES TO ROW/COLUMN ADDRESSES, AND VICE VERSA.

     TO GET BACK TO THE MENU SCREEN FROM ANY OF THE OPTION SCREENS,
   SIMPLY PRESS THE PA1 (ATTN) KEY.  ANOTHER WAY OF DOING THIS IS TO
   ENTER =X AND PRESS ENTER.  IN FACT, YOU CAN GET AROUND IN "AR" IF
   YOU CAN REMEMBER THE OPTION NUMBERS BY ENTERING AN = SIGN FOLLOWED
   BY THE OPTION NUMBER AND PRESSING ENTER.  =0 WILL RETURN TO TSO.

)O    OPERANDS - NONE, OTHER THAN AS SPECIFIED ABOVE
